# Seth's AI Tools - Unity Project Overview

This is a Unity-based front-end for ComfyUI and Ollama that generates photos, movies, Twine games, quizzes, posters and more. The project is a native Windows .exe application that connects to AI services.

## Main Entry Points

- [GameLogic.cs](mdc:Assets/_Script/GameLogic.cs) - Main game logic and application flow
- [Config.cs](mdc:Assets/_Script/Config.cs) - Configuration management and settings
- [PicMain.cs](mdc:Assets/_Script/Pic/PicMain.cs) - Core image generation and processing
- [AIGuideManager.cs](mdc:Assets/_Script/AIGuideManager.cs) - AI Guide feature for creating content

## Key Directories

### Core Scripts
- `Assets/_Script/` - Main application scripts
- `Assets/_Script/GUI/` - User interface components
- `Assets/_Script/Pic/` - Image generation and processing
- `Assets/RT/` - Runtime utilities and core systems
- `Assets/RT/AI/` - AI service integrations (OpenAI, Anthropic, ComfyUI)

### Experiments
- `Assets/Experiments/` - Built-in games and test applications
- `Assets/Experiments/Adventure/` - Twine game generation
- `Assets/Experiments/ShootingGallery/` - AI-powered shooting gallery
- `Assets/Experiments/CrazyCam/` - Real-time webcam processing
- `Assets/Experiments/Pizza/` - Image processing experiments

### Configuration
- [config.txt](mdc:config.txt) - Application configuration file
- `ComfyUI/` - ComfyUI workflow templates and presets
- `Presets/` - User-created presets and settings

## Architecture

The application follows a modular Unity architecture:
- **GameLogic**: Central coordinator and state management
- **PicMain**: Image generation pipeline and UI
- **AIGuideManager**: Content creation features
- **RT Utilities**: Core runtime systems and utilities
- **AI Integrations**: Service-specific managers for different AI providers

## Key Features

- ComfyUI workflow execution and management
- Multiple AI service support (OpenAI, Anthropic, local LLMs)
- Image generation, editing, and processing
- Content creation (stories, quizzes, games)
- Real-time webcam processing
- Drag-and-drop image handling
- Preset system for workflows and settings
